commit_list.message:
Always check presence of an href in a link tag

Some link tags have been discovered without an href. These should
not be returned as valid feed urls
Add RentalSerializer and refactor rental specs
Add polygon/neighborhood factories, spec out neighborhood association
Refactor auth into Authentication service object

Add test for <LogIn /><Form />

* Install jest-localstorage-mock to support testing JWT persistence

Adjust eslint rules:

* Disable imports/first
* Disable no-underscore-dangle
Update tests to use Jest API

Add polyfill for requestAnimationFrame so React 16 works with
jsdom in tests

Invoke Jest from npm script

* Configure Jest to run env.js to setup test environment
Add jest to eslint config environment

Add comma-dangle rule override to be more specific about when to require
dangling commas, and to ignore requiring dangling commas for functions

Uninstall Mocha and Expect

* Remove jsdom setup

Upgrade React to 16.1.1

* Also upgrade react-dom to 16.1.1

Add <UserMenu />

* Add currentUser query
* Conditionally display login/logout actions based on currentUser
* Display link to /podcasts when logged in
* Add log out function to clear clientside auth token only (for now)

Adjust <LoggedIn /> layout

* Create layout theme and add gutters
* Extend common <H2 /> to remove margin for page header
Redirect to <Dashboard /> when log in succeeds

Move Apollo config to its own module

* Update Webpack aliases to add shortcut to /config
* Re-order aliases

Add <LogIn /> page and form

* Store JWT in localStorage

Set up login

* Configure Guardian
* Set up Context plug to set current user
* Add login mutation
Add title to Sign Up page

Reset client side app styles

* Install styled-normalize
* Load normalize.css using injectGlobal
* Add border-box global reset to use the saner box model

Set up theme in js

* Add /theme/colors
* Add /theme/typography
* Inject @font-face declarations globally
* Update .eslintrc to allow template tag literals
Give up on Flow for now

Update <SignUpForm /> to accept result with errors

* Update SignUp mutation
* Store errors in local state
* Display inline error

Update the SignUp mutation to return errors

* Introduce user_result type to encapsulate user and error types

Set up Sign Up page

* Set up Apollo client
* Pull CSRF token from <meta /> and configure Apollo to use it
* Set up React Router
* Add /pages/SignUp and <SignUpForm />

Prepare GraphQL /api endpoint to accept user mutations

* Add Resolvers.Accounts.create/2
* Move Wholoo.DataCase.errors_on to Wholoo.Utils so validation error
  traversal can be used outside of tests
Install react apollo-client, react-apollo and react-router-dom

Add Accounts.User.registration_changeset/2

* Add password virtual attribute
* Hash password using Argon2
* Clean up AccountsTest
Add validations for email format and uniqueness

Add helpers for static Phoenix pages in `LayoutView`

* Add `title/2` to generate page titles from the view module name.
* Add `body_class/1` to generate class names for the body element
  from the view module and template names.
* Add `view_name/1` to get the parameterized view module name,
  for use by `body_class/1`.
* Add `template_name` to get the name of the current template without
  extension

Configure Webpack file-loader to handle images and fonts

* IMPORTANT: The static path in the file-loader Webpack config must begin
  with a `/` because Phoenix.Digester pattern matches on this to
  generate fingerprinted URLs

Serve assets from priv/static, not webpack-dev-server for simplicity.
webpack-dev-server isn't needed since Phoenix is already watching for
changes.

* Uninstall webpack-dev-server
* Call Webpack from Phoenix dev watcher
* Remove references to webpack-dev-server localhost:8080 from templates
* Update buildpack compile script to use priv/static as default source
  and target directories

Separate static landing page from app page

* Add AppController
* Remove bundled CSS from `app.html.eex`
* Add `page.html.eex`

Add custom fonts

* Install file-loader
* Add Lato Regular/Bold and Quattrocento Sans Regular/Bold

Install and set up copy-webpack-plugin

* Copy images & other static assets from assets/static to priv/bundles
Rename app.css to stylesheet.css in app.html.eex

Update heroku-buildpack-phoenix-static compile script

* Pull bundled assets from `priv/bundles`
* Output fingerprinted assets to `priv/static`
Update Webpack to output bundled, but not fingerprinted assets to /priv/bundles/
Run Webpack during compile step in buildpack
Ignore node_modules/styled-components in .flowconfig for now to suppress errors
Install flow-typed and add type definitions

Add Webpack aliases

* Install babel-plugin-webpack-alias
* Set up aliases to component and theme directories
* Add this package as a test env plugin in .babelrc
* Install eslint-import-resolver-webpack and add "import/resolver" config
  to .eslintrc so that Webpack aliases can be resolved by the linter

Add simple styling to <Composer /> to demo Styled Components

* Create theme file
* Install polished

Set up test environment

* Install Mocha, Expect, Enzyme (w/ react-test-renderer & jsdom),
  and fetch-mock
* Configure test environment to use jsdom (assets/js/spec/setup.js)
* Expose React, shallow, mount, expect, etc. in test files
  (assets/js/spec/globals.js)

Set up React app

* Install react, react-dom, babel-react-preset
* Configure Babel to transpile jsx

Configure Webpack to handle basic js

* Add barebones webpack.config.js with Babel enabled
* Set up webpack-dev-server with hot reloading
Close idle websocket connections before Heroku's timeout

Set up Enzyme

* Remove previous Jest snapshot test
* Do not install jest-serialize-enzyme due to a broken dependency
* Therefore do not perform snapshot tests using Enzyme

Display updated at timestamp in <Posts /><Item />

* Cache timezone in <Main />
Use global config params as default props in <Main />

Clean up

* Move <Main /> out of screens/ directory
* Rename <Lyst /> to <Posts />
Add FEED_URL and POSTS_COUNT config params

Build out <Lyst /> component tree

* Fetch single page of data for now
* Add styled components and use in <Item />
Totally missed adding CORS configuration for SSL
Only customize the override file, according to OpsWorks docs
Update spec to use RSpec 3 api
Rewrite to make root path and ignoring params the default behavior
Return errors when there aren't enough values on the stack
Add spec to test chained operations
Improve readability of CLI spec file
Break out concerns to separate classes
Allow values and operators to be entered on one line
Allow exiting when 'q' or '\cD' is entered

Introduce adding

* Set up CLI testing pattern
Add simple loop to read input
Minor improvement to resets example html
Set up html examples for resets

Includes 200+ optional plugins (rails, git, OSX, hub, capistrano, brew, ant, php, python, etc), over 140 themes to spice up your morning, and an auto-update tool so that makes it easy to keep up with the latest updates from the community.
Opsworks sidekiq cookbook for Ubuntu and Rails or non-rails sidekiq deploys
A React Dropzone for File Uploads (using Dropzone.js)
Sample Rails app with server-rendered React components
